FBIS4-23574 "drafr112_d_94006" FBIS-AFR-94-112 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Angola Roundup of Government-UNITA Clashes 9-10 Jun Roundup of Government-UNITA Clashes 9-10 Jun Government Planes Kill 16 in Huambo MB1006085794 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in Portuguese 0600 GMT 10 Jun 94 MB1006085794 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro Portuguese BFN [Text] Huambo residents are still victims of the excessive ambition of the leading class of the Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola-Labor Party, which orders the bombing of the city everyday. On 8 June at least 12 napalm and incendiary bombs were dropped on Huambo, killing 16 people and wounding 35, including women, children, and old people. A communique issued by the Armed Forces for the Liberation of Angola General Staff, signed by General Arlindo Chenda Pena Ben-Ben, during the 8 June air raid, reports that 23 people were burned. The killings were executed by Su aircraft coming from the Catumbela Air Base.
